oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Entering Cherokee National Forest
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Road entering the Cherokee National Forest, located in Greene County, Tennessee. The road disappears into the mountains in the background. A wooden building [barn], fences, and plowed fields line the road. A signpost in foreground indicates the entrance.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
